Re-uploading an old exercise with a strong focus on performant C++.

An order book is a data structure that allows asks/bid requests to be
stored, matched, removed.

In this example we build a cache-friendly structure able to reasonabily perform on the nanosecond scale,
having fun and feeling the pleasure of speed.

Since this was merely an exercise, there is no appropriate documentation / testing.

